article.headline: Indiana St. 69, Toledo 62
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Jay Tunnell scored 17 points Saturday and Indiana State beat Toledo 69-62 for its fifth straight victory, the Sycamores' longest winning streak in two years. Indiana State (9-19) took the lead early in the first half and built the margin to 32-24 at halftime. A basket and free throw by Harry Marshall put the Sycamores up 58-48, and Toledo never came closer than seven the rest of the game. Marshall finished with 16 points, while Rashad Reed added 15 and Jordan Printy finished with 13 for the Sycamores. The Rockets were led by Tyrone Kent with 16 points and nine rebounds and Jonathan Amos with 15 points.
